cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on benchmarking state-of-the-art methods for forecasting electricity demand on the household level, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with Smart Grids, which are complex systems that involve control and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different forecasting methods and strategies, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
